gitops/argocd 
----------------------

create one cluster , ng 
one client instance to connect 

kubectl install
-------------------
curl -LO https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.29.0/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl

chmod +x kubectl

sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/

kubectl version --client

configure 
-------------
aws configure  or you can add iam role 
add access key and secret key 


aws eks update-kubeconfig --region us-east-1 --name <clustername>

install argocd
--------------------

kubectl create namespace argocd   ----> argocd namespace created 

kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml   ---->install argocd

kubectl get all -n argocd         ---------->to see the pods 

kubectl edit svc argocd-server -n argocd  #enable Node Port
  change the cluster ip to NodePort svc

kubectl get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -n argocd -o yaml 
  decode the secret password   echo "secret value" | base64 --decode

how to access the argocd
-----------------------------------
 kubectl get all -n argocd
	(see in which port the argocd server is running )

 kubectl get nodes 
  
access
------
externalip : argocd serverport  

enter username :admin
password : decoded password

argocd inside 
------------

new app
give an application name 
project name : default 
sync policy : automatic 
give repo url : 
path 
and name space 
create 

if you have image inside the eks then use the image in the iamge in yaml file 

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-deployment
  labels:
    app: nginx
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: 211739080894.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/hotstar-nodejs-project:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: nginx-loadbalancer
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: nginx
  ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 3000       # External port   
      targetPort: 3000 # Container port  <you can change the ports 80 >

---------------
if you give another port then use that port after the load balancer
